## PAGE ARCHITECTURE — SECTION BY SECTION

### 0. NAVIGATION (Sticky, minimal)

```
[ilmundo logo wordmark]    [Services] [About] [Why ilmundo] [Contact]    [Get Started →]
```

- Logo: wordmark in `var(--font-display)`, italic style, dark ink
- Nav bg: transparent → `rgba(255,242,233,0.92)` (#FFF2E9 tinted) + backdrop blur on scroll
- "Get Started" CTA: pill button, `background: #012A8C`, cream text `#FFF2E9` — on cream nav bg. On blue hero: inverted, cream bg + blue text.
- Mobile: hamburger → full-screen overlay menu with large type

---

### 1. HERO SECTION

**Layout:** Full-width, `background: var(--section-blue)` (#012A8C, deep cobalt), cream/white text. Large editorial headline left-aligned, supporting copy right. The logo's globe grid motif appears large and ghost-like on the right (~40% opacity, cream-colored) — this is the single most important decorative element on the page. It signals the brand's visual language immediately.

**Headline (H1):**
```
Knowledge
Without Borders.
```
*Render in `var(--font-display)`, italic, massive — `var(--text-hero)`, color: `var(--color-cream)` (#FFF2E9), `letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight)`*

**Sub-headline:**
```
Premium education consulting rooted in Malaysian values,
shaped by a global perspective.
```
*`var(--font-body)`, weight 300, 1.125rem, `color: rgba(255,242,233,0.75)`*

**CTAs (two, side by side):**
- Primary: "Explore Our Services" → cream pill button (`#FFF2E9`), blue text (`#012A8C`)
- Secondary: "Meet the Founder →" → ghost/text link, cream color, underline on hover

**Bottom of hero:** Floating label strip:
```
[✦ Academic Tuition] [✦ University Admissions] [✦ Global Education Concierge] [✦ Coming Soon: 8 More Services]
```
Horizontal scroll on mobile. Pill badges: `background: rgba(255,242,233,0.15)`, `border: 1px solid rgba(255,242,233,0.3)`, cream text.

**Background detail:** Faint globe grid watermark at `opacity: 0.06`, cream color, large-scale — derived from the logo mark. The M-mountain silhouette can also appear subtly as a topographic contour at the bottom edge of the section.

